{
  "analysis": "od cannot skip to those file offsets directly, likely because the binary is not seekable in that mode or addresses are virtual addresses not file offsets. I need to use objdump -s to dump the .rodata section and map virtual addresses to contents, or use dd with section file offsets from readelf.",
  "plan": "Use readelf to find section file offsets and virtual addresses for .rodata/.data, then dump the relevant constants. Also use perl to parse the PPM and sample pixels.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "readelf -S /app/mystery | grep -E 'rodata|data|Name|Nr|\\.text'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "objdump -s -j .rodata /app/mystery | sed -n '1,60p'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "perl -e 'open(F,\"/app/image.ppm\"); my $h=<F>; my $d=<F>; my $m=<F>; print \"$h$d$m\"; my @p; while(<F>){push @p,split;} print \"total=\",scalar(@p),\"\\n\"; sub px{my($x,$y)=@_; my $i=($y*800+$x)*3; return ($p[$i],$p[$i+1],$p[$i+2]);} for my $y (0,150,300,450,599){ for my $x (0,200,400,600,799){ print \"($x,$y): \",join(\" \",px($x,$y)),\"\\n\";}}'\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
